abstract = {Over the last decades, industries have shifted from a mass production model to a mass customization paradigm. The advances in manufacturing and information technologies facilitate the cost-efficient design, development, and manufacturing of products. Nowadays, consumers are looking for more product variants and configurations in a massive way. The pressure for increased product customization is often high and, therefore, manufacturing companies and networks cannot cope with the additional complexity. Many manufacturing companies are still challenged into taking full advantage of product data and lifecycle management systems. This chapter delves into how modern digital manufacturing technologies with advanced product information and lifecycle management platforms may be utilized for reducing and eventually taming the complexity in production systems and networks. Furthermore, the key challenges for employing digital technologies under the Industry 4.0 framework are discussed. The chapter concludes with how future technologies will support humans’ decision-making as part of the product development process.}
}
